{# ═══ §I · THE MODEL ════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}

{# ─── Chart 1 · The Power Law Channel (±2y default) ──────────────── #}
<section class="gallery-section" id="section-channel" aria-labelledby="title-channel">
    <div class="gallery-section-inner">
        <header class="gallery-section-header">
            <p class="gallery-section-eyebrow">&sect;I &middot; The Model &middot; Chart 1 of 10</p>
            <h2 id="title-channel" class="gallery-section-title">The Power Law Channel</h2>
            <p class="gallery-section-subtitle">Where bitcoin sits right now in the channel &mdash; trend, floor, ceiling, and the next two years.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="range-toggle" role="tablist" aria-label="Chart time range">
            <button type="button" class="range-btn" data-range="all-time" role="tab" aria-selected="false">All-time</button>
            <button type="button" class="range-btn" data-range="near" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Near (&plusmn;1y)</button>
            <button type="button" class="range-btn active" data-range="planning" role="tab" aria-selected="true">Planning (&plusmn;2y)</button>
        </div>

        <div class="gallery-chart-frame">
            <canvas id="galleryChannelChart" aria-label="Power Law channel chart"></canvas>
            <div class="gallery-chart-fallback" aria-hidden="true">
                <p class="chart-loading">Loading the channel&hellip;</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gallery-chart-status" id="channelStatus">
            <span class="status-label">Today (live):</span>
            <span class="status-price" id="channelTodayPrice">&mdash;</span>
            <span class="status-sep">&middot;</span>
            <span class="status-multiple" id="channelTodayMult">&mdash;</span>
        </div>

        <div class="gallery-section-prose">
            <p>The Power Law channel is the structural model that anchors most of the quantitative arguments on this site. The solid line is bitcoin&rsquo;s <em>trend</em> price under proportional (not exponential) growth; the dashed lines bound a <em>floor</em> at 0.42&times; trend and an <em>upper band</em> at 3&times; trend &mdash; a range price has rarely strayed beyond across fifteen years and nine orders of magnitude.</p>
            <p>The &plusmn;2y view zooms to decision-relevant time. Where the price is <em>right now</em> relative to the channel is the question most people are actually asking when they look at this chart &mdash; the all-time log-log view is what proves the model; this is what makes it actionable.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="gallery-section-source">More in this exploration &rarr; <a href="/the-power-law.html#channel">Bitcoin &amp; the Power Law</a></p>
    </div>
</section>


{# ─── Chart 2 · Power Law Implied CAGR vs. S&P 500 ────────────────── #}
<section class="gallery-section" id="section-cagr" aria-labelledby="title-cagr">
    <div class="gallery-section-inner">
        <header class="gallery-section-header">
            <p class="gallery-section-eyebrow">&sect;I &middot; The Model &middot; Chart 2 of 10</p>
            <h2 id="title-cagr" class="gallery-section-title">Power Law Implied CAGR vs. S&amp;P 500</h2>
            <p class="gallery-section-subtitle">What the model projects, year by starting year, against the equity benchmark.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="gallery-chart-frame">
            <canvas id="galleryCagrChart" aria-label="Power Law implied CAGR vs S&P 500 bar chart"></canvas>
            <div class="gallery-chart-fallback" aria-hidden="true">
                <p class="chart-loading">Loading the comparison&hellip;</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gallery-section-prose">
            <p>The Power Law implies a specific annualized return from each starting year. Each bar is the model's projected CAGR through 2035 for a bitcoin purchase made in that year; the dashed line is the S&amp;P 500's historical ~10% annual average. Even at the conservative end &mdash; buying in 2030 &mdash; the model's implied CAGR through 2035 is roughly <em>three times</em> the equity benchmark.</p>
            <p class="prose-footnote"><em>On convergence:</em> Bitcoin's CAGR declines as the model decelerates, but never crosses the S&amp;P 500's historical 10% within any reasonable forecast horizon. Even projecting from 2025 to 2150, the implied annualized return remains around 10%. The chart's window shows the strongest period of relative outperformance &mdash; but the gap, while shrinking, persists for decades beyond it.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="gallery-section-source">More in this exploration &rarr; <a href="/the-power-law.html">Bitcoin &amp; the Power Law</a></p>
    </div>
</section>


{# ═══ §II · REAL-WORLD DENOMINATIONS ═══════════════════════════════ #}

{# ─── Chart 3 · BTC Required to Buy the Median US House ──────────── #}
<section class="gallery-section" id="section-btc-house" aria-labelledby="title-btc-house">
    <div class="gallery-section-inner">
        <header class="gallery-section-header">
            <p class="gallery-section-eyebrow">&sect;II &middot; Real-World Denominations &middot; Chart 3 of 10</p>
            <h2 id="title-btc-house" class="gallery-section-title">BTC Required to Buy the Median US House</h2>
            <p class="gallery-section-subtitle">Annual averages, 2013&ndash;2025 actual, with projected trend to 2032 &mdash; log scale.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="gallery-chart-frame">
            <canvas id="galleryBtcHouseChart" aria-label="BTC required to buy the median US house"></canvas>
            <div class="gallery-chart-fallback" aria-hidden="true">
                <p class="chart-loading">Loading the trajectory&hellip;</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gallery-section-prose">
            <p>In 2013, you needed <em>367 bitcoin</em> to buy the median US house. By 2025, you needed roughly <em>5</em>. That's a 98.6% decline in the bitcoin-denominated cost of housing across twelve years. Yes, the line is volatile &mdash; bitcoin is volatile &mdash; but look at the direction. No amount of fiat appreciation in home values can disguise what is happening on this chart.</p>
            <p>The house is demonetizing &mdash; shedding its store-of-value premium &mdash; as bitcoin absorbs the monetary energy that was artificially trapped in real estate. The dashed line is where the historical trend points to next, not a price prediction.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="gallery-section-source">More in this exploration &rarr; <a href="/bitcoin-vs-real-estate.html#priced-in-bitcoin">Bitcoin vs. Real Estate</a></p>
    </div>
</section>


